### Phase 7 — post-ship fix (2026-05-28)

`startTransition` called during render — three widgets patched.

- `AgentTasksWidget`, `ManagerLeadStatusWidget`, `ManagerCampaignWidget` — initial fetch moved into `useEffect`; `cancelled` flag prevents stale state update on unmount
- **Rule:** Initial data fetch in any widget must live in `useEffect` + `startTransition` + `cancelled` flag. Never call `startTransition` in the render phase.
- **Limitation:** the `cancelled` flag only guards against `setState` on an unmounted component — it does not cancel the in-flight server action. Acceptable for fast read-only actions. If a future widget mounts a slow or expensive action, consider `AbortController` + a `signal` param on the server action. Do not pre-engineer this.

